<p>The area from Tottenham Court Road to Holborn is known as Bloomsbury. We 
start by walking up Tottenham Court Road and turn right into Great Russell 
Street. Bedford Square is the most complete Georgian Square in Bloomsbury. We 
admire the bizarre church of
<a href="http://www.stgeorgesbloomsbury.org.uk/" target="_blank">St George</a>, 
with its pyramidical steeple topped by a statue of George I dressed in a toga.</p>
