<p>The medical area of Queen Square and
<a href="http://www.ich.ucl.ac.uk/" target="_blank">Great Ormond Street</a> come 
next, leading to Doughty Street and the
<a href="http://www.hiddenlondon.com/dickensh.htm" target="_blank">Dickens House 
Museum</a>. This is one of many associations with Charles Dickens and his 
contemporary novelist
<a href="http://www.fantasticfiction.co.uk/t/anthony-trollope/" target="_blank">
Anthony Trollope</a> throughout the walk.</p>
<p>We finish at Russell Square
<a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk/tube/" target="_blank">Underground</a> (zone 1).</p>
